<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Assignment on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/assignment/</link><description>Recent content in Assignment on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/assignment/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Pascal: type mismatch error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/pascal/pascal-type-mismatch-v2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/pascal/pascal-type-mismatch-v2/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pascal type mismatch errors occur when assigning a value of one type to a variable of an incompatible type, or when comparing incompatible types.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assigning string to integer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comparing incompatible types&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wrong parameter type in function call&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implicit conversion failure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Variant type mismatch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-gdscript3" data-lang="gdscript3"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;program TypeMismatch;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; x: Integer;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;begin
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; x :&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Hello&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;//&lt;/span&gt; Error: string to integer
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;end&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-gdscript3" data-lang="gdscript3"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;program SafeConversion;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; x: Integer;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; s: string;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;begin
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; s :&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;42&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; x :&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; StrToInt(s); &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;//&lt;/span&gt; Explicit conversion
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; WriteLn(x);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;end&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-gdscript3" data-lang="gdscript3"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;program TypeChecking;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; a: Integer;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; b: Real;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;begin
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; a :&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; b :&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3.14&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;//&lt;/span&gt; Don&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;t mix types in comparisons&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; a &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; Round(b) then
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; WriteLn(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Equal&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;end&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-gdscript3" data-lang="gdscript3"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;program SafeAssignment;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; v: Variant;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; i: Integer;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;begin
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; v :&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; VarIsNumeric(v) then
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; begin
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; i :&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; v; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;//&lt;/span&gt; Safe conversion
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; WriteLn(i);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; end;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;end&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-gdscript3" data-lang="gdscript3"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;program FunctionParams;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;function Add(a, b: Integer): Integer;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;begin
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Add :&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; a &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; b;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;end;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; x: Integer;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;begin
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; x :&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; Add(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;20&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;//&lt;/span&gt; Correct types
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; WriteLn(x);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;end&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="pascal-runtime-error-v2"&gt;Runtime Error&lt;/a&gt; - general runtime&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="pascal-index-out-of-range-v2"&gt;Index Out of Range&lt;/a&gt; - bounds errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="pascal-exception-error-v2"&gt;Exception Error&lt;/a&gt; - exception handling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Python SyntaxError — Starred Assignment Target Must Be In List or Tuple</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/star-expression/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/star-expression/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="syntaxerror--starred-assignment-target-must-be-in-list-or-tuple"&gt;SyntaxError — Starred Assignment Target Must Be In List or Tuple&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;SyntaxError&lt;/code&gt; with the message &amp;ldquo;starred assignment target must be in a list or tuple&amp;rdquo; is raised when you use a starred expression (&lt;code&gt;*variable&lt;/code&gt;) as a standalone assignment target instead of inside a list or tuple. Star expressions can only appear in unpacking contexts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Star expressions (&lt;code&gt;*variable&lt;/code&gt;) are used for extended iterable unpacking. They capture &amp;ldquo;remaining&amp;rdquo; elements from a sequence. However, they must appear inside a list &lt;code&gt;[...]&lt;/code&gt;, tuple &lt;code&gt;(...)&lt;/code&gt;, or as part of a function call. Using &lt;code&gt;*variable&lt;/code&gt; as a direct assignment target is not allowed.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Python SyntaxError — Walrus Operator Invalid Syntax</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/walrus-operator/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/walrus-operator/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="syntaxerror--walrus-operator-invalid-syntax"&gt;SyntaxError — Walrus Operator Invalid Syntax&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;SyntaxError&lt;/code&gt; with the message &amp;ldquo;invalid syntax&amp;rdquo; when using the walrus operator &lt;code&gt;:=&lt;/code&gt; is raised when you use this operator in a context where it&amp;rsquo;s not allowed, or when using it in Python versions before 3.8. The walrus operator was introduced in Python 3.8 (PEP 572).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The walrus operator &lt;code&gt;:=&lt;/code&gt; allows assignment expressions inside other expressions. It assigns a value to a variable as part of a larger expression. However, it has restrictions: it cannot be used at the top level, in function arguments (in some contexts), or in certain other positions.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Python ValueError — Not Enough Values to Unpack</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/unpack-non-sequence/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/unpack-non-sequence/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="valueerror--not-enough-values-to-unpack"&gt;ValueError — Not Enough Values to Unpack&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;ValueError&lt;/code&gt; with the message &amp;ldquo;not enough values to unpack&amp;rdquo; is raised when you try to unpack a sequence into more variables than the sequence contains. The number of variables must match the number of elements, or you must use starred expressions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sequence unpacking assigns elements of a sequence to variables. Python requires the number of variables to match the number of elements, unless you use &lt;code&gt;*&lt;/code&gt; to capture remaining elements. This error is common when data has unexpected length.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>